main event: Observers in Duluth witnessed a white point of light in the sky, suspected to be the ECHO II satellite.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling toward the northeast for about 5 minutes., The sighting occurred near the zenith of the sky., The observers included a tavern owner and another individual named George Verzich., The report concluded the object was likely a satellite., The weather was reported as clear during the sighting.
sighted object: a white point of light in the sky
